In a mixing bowl, combine turkey, chili powder, cumin, and salt. Shape into 4 patties. Spray cold grill and utensils well with grilling spray. Position grill 3 to 4 inches from heat. Heat grill according to manufacturer's suggestion. Cook patties over medium heat about 15 minutes or until done. Spray cut side of buns with cooking spray for 8 seconds total; place face down and grill until golden. Squeeze lemon over lettuce, tomato and avocado. Serve each turkey burger on a bun; top with vegetables.